 for a nonthermal synchrotron emission component. The temperature and\ncharacteristic emission-region size of the blackbody component are found to,\nrespectively, decrease and increase as power laws with time during the prompt\nphase. In addition, we find that the blackbody and nonthermal components have\nseparate temporal behaviors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Apr 2013 21:19:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Dec 2013 20:32:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-04"}
